{"title":"Setgid","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Setgid","type":"markdown","data":"[![Unix manual pages](/images/b/bf/Man_icon.png)](/wiki/File:Man_icon.png \"Unix manual pages\")\n\n[Unix](/wiki/Unix \"Unix\") manual for **setgid(2):**\n\n- [FreeBSD](https://www.freebsd.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=setgid\\&sektion=2)\n- [NetBSD](https://man.netbsd.org/cgi-bin/man-cgi?setgid+2)\n- [OpenBSD](https://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=setgid\\&sektion=2)\n- [Linux](https://linux.die.net/man/2/setgid)\n\n[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\") needs to be able to write files into a directory called the [playground](/wiki/Playground \"Playground\"). This is necessary to save games, to delete saved games when loading them, to save [persistent levels](/wiki/Persistent_level \"Persistent level\") during gameplay, to log games, and to add to the list of high scores. However, on multiuser [Unix](/wiki/Unix \"Unix\") systems, users should not have write permision to the playground *except* when they play NetHack. Why let users cheat, or worse, corrupt the saves of other users?\n\nThe solution is to give write access for the playground not to the users, but to a special Unix group such as `games`. Then [chown](http://www.freebsd.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=chown) the executable to user `root`, group `games` and set the **setgid** bit. When the game starts, the system will *set* the effective *g*roup *id* to `games` and NetHack will have the privileges necessary to write to the [playground](/wiki/Playground \"Playground\").\n\nThis sort of arrangement dates back to [Hack](/wiki/Hack \"Hack\"), which needed this setup for the same reasons as NetHack does. Here is [Hack 1.0.3](/wiki/Hack_1.0.3 \"Hack 1.0.3\") upon [Kernigh](/wiki/User:Kernigh \"User:Kernigh\")'s [OpenBSD](/wiki/OpenBSD \"OpenBSD\") system:\n\n```\n$ ls -l /usr/games/hack\n-r-xr-sr-x  1 root  games  250568 Mar  1  2006 /usr/games/hack\n$ ls -ld /var/games/hackdir\ndrwxrwxr-x  3 root  games  512 Jul 18 15:50 /var/games/hackdir\n```\n\nA user has suggested improving this page or section as follows:\n\n*\"Perhaps someone should edit the page and provide this info for their NetHack installation. Note that the `nethack` command is a shell script and that the setgid executable might be in the playground somewhere.\"*\n\nThe \"s\" in \"-r-xr-sr-x\" indicates that **setgid** is set. The group of the setgid executable (here /usr/games/hack) and that of the playground (here /var/games/hackdir) must match.\n\n[![This article is unlikely to require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.](/images/5/58/Noversion.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article is unlikely to require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Setgid - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Setgid\",\"wgTitle\":\"Setgid\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":170986,\"wgRevisionId\":170986,\"wgArticleId\":4696,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Todo\",\"Development\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Setgid\",\"wgRelevantArticleId\":4696,\"wgRequestId\":\"7ea9e6bc68218a444535d8a0\",\"wgCSPNonce\":false,\"wgIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRelevantPageIsProbablyEditable\":false,\"wgRestrictionEdit\":[],\"wgRestrictionMove\":[],\"wgWikiEditorEnabledModules\":[],\"wgCategoryTreePageCategoryOptions\":\"{\\\"mode\\\":0,\\\"hideprefix\\\":20,\\\"showcount\\\":true,\\\"namespaces\\\":false}\"});mw.loader.state({\"site.styles\":\"ready\",\"noscript\":\"ready\",\"user.styles\":\"ready\",\"user\":\"ready\",\"user.options\":\"ready\",\"user.tokens\":\"loading\",\"mediawiki.legacy.shared\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint\":\"ready\",\"mediawiki.skinning.interface\":\"ready\",\"skins.vector.styles\":\"ready\"});mw.loader.implement(\"user.tokens@0tffind\",function($,jQuery,require,module){/*@nomin*/mw.user.tokens.set({\"editToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"patrolToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"watchToken\":\"+\\\\\",\"csrfToken\":\"+\\\\\"});\n});RLPAGEMODULES=[\"site\",\"mediawiki.page.startup\",\"mediawiki.user\",\"mediawiki.page.ready\",\"mediawiki.searchSuggest\",\"skins.vector.js\"];mw.loader.load(RLPAGEMODULES);});</script>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=mediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmediawiki.skinning.interface%7Cskins.vector.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<script async=\"\" src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=startup&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector\"></script>\n<meta name=\"ResourceLoaderDynamicStyles\" content=\"\"/>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=site.styles&amp;only=styles&amp;skin=vector\"/>\n<meta name=\"generator\" content=\"MediaWiki 1.32.5\"/>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"NetHack needs to be able to write files into a directory called the playground. This is necessary to save games, to delete saved games when loading them, to save persistent levels during gameplay, to log games, and to add to the list of high scores. However, on multiuser Unix systems, users should not have write permision to the playground except when they play NetHack. Why let users cheat, or worse, corrupt the saves of other users?\"/>\n<link rel=\"image_src\" href=\"/images/6/65/Nethackwiki-logo.png\"/>\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/images/6/64/Favicon.ico\"/>\n<link rel=\"search\" type=\"application/opensearchdescription+xml\" href=\"/opensearch_desc.php\" title=\"NetHackWiki\"/>\n<link rel=\"EditURI\" type=\"application/rsd+xml\" href=\"https://nethackwiki.com/api.php?action=rsd\"/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"/wiki/Setgid\"/>\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src=\"/load.php?debug=false&amp;lang=en&amp;modules=html5shiv&amp;only=scripts&amp;skin=vector&amp;sync=1\"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class=\"mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Setgid rootpage-Setgid skin-vector action-view\">\t\t<div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Setgid</h1>\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From NetHackWiki</div>\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#p-search\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"noprint sidebox\" style=\"clear: right; border: solid #aaa 1px; margin: 0 0 1em 1em; font-size: 90%; background: #f9f9f9; width: 250px; padding: 4px; spacing: 0px; text-align: left; float: right;\">\n<div style=\"float: left;\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Man_icon.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"Unix manual pages\"><img alt=\"Unix manual pages\" src=\"/images/b/bf/Man_icon.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" /></a></div></div>\n<div style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Unix\" title=\"Unix\">Unix</a> manual for <b>setgid(2):</b>\n<ul><li><a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.freebsd.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=setgid&amp;sektion=2\">FreeBSD</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://man.netbsd.org/cgi-bin/man-cgi?setgid+2\">NetBSD</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/man.cgi?query=setgid&amp;sektion=2\">OpenBSD</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://linux.die.net/man/2/setgid\">Linux</a></li></ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/NetHack\" title=\"NetHack\">NetHack</a> needs to be able to write files into a directory called the <a href=\"/wiki/Playground\" title=\"Playground\">playground</a>. This is necessary to save games, to delete saved games when loading them, to save <a href=\"/wiki/Persistent_level\" title=\"Persistent level\">persistent levels</a> during gameplay, to log games, and to add to the list of high scores. However, on multiuser <a href=\"/wiki/Unix\" title=\"Unix\">Unix</a> systems, users should not have write permision to the playground <i>except</i> when they play NetHack. Why let users cheat, or worse, corrupt the saves of other users?\n</p><p>The solution is to give write access for the playground not to the users, but to a special Unix group such as <tt>games</tt>. Then <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.freebsd.org/cgi/man.cgi?query=chown\">chown</a> the executable to user <tt>root</tt>, group <tt>games</tt> and set the <b>setgid</b> bit. When the game starts, the system will <i>set</i> the effective <i>g</i>roup <i>id</i> to <tt>games</tt> and NetHack will have the privileges necessary to write to the <a href=\"/wiki/Playground\" title=\"Playground\">playground</a>.\n</p><p>This sort of arrangement dates back to <a href=\"/wiki/Hack\" title=\"Hack\">Hack</a>, which needed this setup for the same reasons as NetHack does. Here is <a href=\"/wiki/Hack_1.0.3\" title=\"Hack 1.0.3\">Hack 1.0.3</a> upon <a href=\"/wiki/User:Kernigh\" title=\"User:Kernigh\">Kernigh</a>'s <a href=\"/wiki/OpenBSD\" title=\"OpenBSD\">OpenBSD</a> system:\n</p>\n<pre>$ ls -l /usr/games/hack\n-r-xr-sr-x  1 root  games  250568 Mar  1  2006 /usr/games/hack\n$ ls -ld /var/games/hackdir\ndrwxrwxr-x  3 root  games  512 Jul 18 15:50 /var/games/hackdir\n</pre>\n<div class=\"todo\">\n<p>A user has suggested improving this page or section as follows:\n</p><p><i>\"Perhaps someone should edit the page and provide this info for their NetHack installation. Note that the <tt>nethack</tt> command is a shell script and that the setgid executable might be in the playground somewhere.\"</i>\n</p>\n</div>\n<p>The \"s\" in \"-r-xr-sr-x\" indicates that <b>setgid</b> is set. The group of the setgid executable (here /usr/games/hack) and that of the playground (here /var/games/hackdir) must match.\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<div style=\"display:none; right:10px; padding-bottom: 17px\" class=\"metadata topicon nopopups\"><div style=\"margin-top: -10px\"><a href=\"/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version\" title=\"This article is unlikely to require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.\"><img alt=\"This article is unlikely to require revision for the next version of NetHack. Click here for more information.\" src=\"/images/5/58/Noversion.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240926190325\nCache expiry: 604800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.013 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.016 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 109/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 668/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 2254/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 548/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 8/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUn